@Grimjaw:  

Don't get me wrong, I love what this aura does when it lands on your guy and he gets in there. But dude, auras are bad. They're dead cards once you have no creatures in play. Equipment also as useless with no creatures in play, unless they're neat like [Batterskull](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Batterskull) and give you a dude to wear crap. It's not so much as people think the effects auras can provide aren't worth the drawback of a well-timed [Doom Blade](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doom Blade), [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), [Into the Roil](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Into the Roil), or [Swords to Plowshares](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares); it's that on their own, in your hand as sorcery-speed things that require a solid target, they're often clunky. Why go through all the trouble of Necromantic Thirst when you can just use a [Sun Titan](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sun Titan), who is frankly more versatile and can win games just by attacking? The name of the game is utility. The less moving parts, the more room you have for other neat things in your deck.  

